  "text": "are periodic functions of retarded time u, if the spacetime is assumed to be timeperiodic in sense of Definition 1.1. As a first consequence of the stronger time-periodicity assumption we state here the time-independence of the lower order curvature components α, β, which cannot be inferred from the weaker no-radiation condition alone. The argument exploits time-periodicity as in [CITATION_1] .",
